Strong's lexicons & tagged tokens — data/strongs/ (SPEC v6)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Work:    Greek + Hebrew Strong's lexicons (lemma, transliteration, gloss,
         definition) and the tagged words of the Greek NT + Hebrew OT
         (position, surface, Strong's, morph)
Source:  STEPBible-Data — TBESG/TBESH (Brief lexicons of Extended Strongs for
         Greek/Hebrew) and TAGNT/TAHOT (Amalgamated Greek NT / Hebrew OT) —
         https://github.com/STEPBible/STEPBible-Data
License: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)

  Lexicon & tagging data created by STEPBible.org based on work at Tyndale House
  Cambridge (the Brief lexicons draw on Abbott-Smith for Greek and BDB for
  Hebrew), licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International
  (CC BY 4.0) license. The underlying Strong's numbering (1890) is public domain.
  Concord keys entries on the collapsed-base Extended Strong's number, strips the
  definition HTML to plain text, and loads them into the strongs_entries table
  (data/strongs/lexicon.json, lexicon-hebrew.json); the SBLGNT + OSHB words become
  tagged tokens in the word_tokens table (data/strongs/tokens-sblgnt.json,
  tokens-oshb.json). All committed and shipped; the raw TBESG/TBESH/TAGNT/TAHOT
  files are re-derivable and not committed (gitignored + dockerignored
  data/original/). STEPBible asks that others refer to github.com/STEPBible as
  the canonical source. See data/SOURCES.md.

